			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span>Police are advising people to be cautious of telephone calls they receive in the wake of an elderly couple being scammed out of nearly $10,000. Police say someone called the Boyertown couple yesterday and claimed to be a relative in need of money for an emergency. The caller convinced the couple to wire the money. Police say they&#8217;ve received reports of others receiving similar calls, but they&#8217;re not aware of anyone else having lost money.</span></p>
